<H1>Package ncurses</H1>
The ncurses unit gives a straight translation of the ncurses library header
files, as well as some extra units, making programming ncurses a bit easier.
Some of these units have been programmed by Ken J. Wright.
<P>
The following units are available:
<UL>
<LI><B>ncurses</B> The actual translation of the ncurses library header
files. (<A
HREF="http://www.freepascal.org/docs-html/packages/ncurses/ncurses">view interface</A>)

<LI><B>nCrt</B> An implementation of the crt unit based on the curses
library. It should be a complete replacement for the standard CRT unit, and
should run on most terminals. (<A
HREF="http://www.freepascal.org/docs-html/packages/ncurses/ncrt">view interface</A>)
<LI><B>oCrt</B> An object oriented wrapper around the CRT unit.(<A
HREF="http://www.freepascal.org/docs-html/packages/ncurses/ocrt">view interface</A>)
<LI><B>menu</B> A unit implementing a menu system.(<A
HREF="http://www.freepascal.org/docs-html/packages/ncurses/menu">view interface</A>)
<LI><B>panel</B> a unit which interfaces to the 'panel' library on linux,
which handles overlapping windows.(<A
HREF="http://www.freepascal.org/docs-html/packages/ncurses/panel">view interface</A>)
</UL>

The following test programs are also available:
<UL>
<LI><B>db_demo</B> ocrt demo for simulated database input.
<LI><B>Edit_Demo</B> ocrt demo - implements an editor.
<LI><B>ocrt_demo</B> simple ocrt demo.
<LI><B>screen_demo</B> Demonstrate Linux screen saving/restoring with oCrt.
<LI><B>testn</B> simple ncrt demo.
<LI><B>firework</B> ncurses demo.
</UL>

